</tr>
<tr>
<th style="background:transparent; line-height:1.1em;">Known&#160;for</th>
<td class="" style="line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle;"><a href="/wiki/Counterfactual_history" title="Counterfactual history">Counterfactual history</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=History_of_finance&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="History of finance (page does not exist)">financial history</a>, <a href="/wiki/Imperialism" title="Imperialism">imperialism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Colonialism" title="Colonialism">colonialism</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Niall Ferguson</b> (born April 18, 1964, in <a href="/wiki/Glasgow" title="Glasgow">Glasgow</a>) is a British <a href="/wiki/Historian" title="Historian">historian</a>. He specialises in <a href="/wiki/Financial" title="Financial" class="mw-redirect">financial</a> and <a href="/wiki/Economic_history" title="Economic history">economic history</a> as well as the <a href="/wiki/History" title="History">history</a> of <a href="/wiki/Empire" title="Empire">empire</a>. He is the <a href="/wiki/Laurence_Tisch" title="Laurence Tisch">Laurence A. Tisch</a> <a href="/wiki/Professor" title="Professor">Professor</a> of History at <a href="/wiki/Harvard_University" title="Harvard University">Harvard University</a> and the William Ziegler Professor of <a href="/wiki/Business_Administration" title="Business Administration" class="mw-redirect">Business Administration</a> at <a href="/wiki/Harvard_Business_School" title="Harvard Business School">Harvard Business School</a>. He was educated at the famous independent school <a href="/wiki/The_Glasgow_Academy" title="The Glasgow Academy">The Glasgow Academy</a> in Scotland, and at <a href="/wiki/Magdalen_College,_Oxford" title="Magdalen College, Oxford">Magdalen College, Oxford</a>.</p>
<p>He is best known outside academia for his revisionist views rehabilitating <a href="/wiki/Imperialism" title="Imperialism">imperialism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Colonialism" title="Colonialism">colonialism</a>; within academia, his championing of <a href="/wiki/Counterfactual_history" title="Counterfactual history">counterfactual history</a> is a subject of some considerable controversy. In 2008, Allen Lane published his most recent book, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Ascent_of_Money:_A_Financial_History_of_the_World" title="The Ascent of Money: A Financial History of the World" class="mw-redirect">The Ascent of Money: A Financial History of the World</a></i><sup id="cite_ref-ascent_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ascent-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> which he also presented as a <a href="/wiki/Channel_4" title="Channel 4">Channel 4</a> television series.</p>
